Package: slick-nat-dkms
Version: 0.0.3
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms (>= 2.2), linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers | linux-headers-$(shell uname -r)
Recommends: build-essential, linux-libc-dev
Suggests: iproute2, iputils-ping, slick-nat-ns
Installed-Size: 1024
Maintainer: Slick NAT Project <lucas@xtec.one>
Description: Slick NAT - Bidirectional IPv6 NAT kernel module
 A high-performance IPv6 NAT kernel module that provides bidirectional
 address translation with dynamic mapping configuration and per-namespace
 support.
 .
 Features:
  * Bidirectional IPv6 NAT with dynamic configuration
  * Per-Network Namespace support for containers
  * Container support (LXD, Docker)
  * Neighbor Discovery Protocol proxy
  * ICMP error handling with embedded packet translation
  * Interface-specific mappings
  * Automatic kernel module rebuilding via DKMS
 .
 This package uses DKMS to automatically build the kernel module for
 your system and rebuild it when kernel updates are installed.
 .
 The module will be automatically loaded on boot and can be managed
 using the slnat command-line tool.
 .
 For container environments, also install slick-nat-ns package.
Homepage: https://github.com/a2hop/slick-nat
